<br>
There is also a question of sanitation.  Overturned graves tend to attract wild animals.  There is also an issue of disease, plague etc.<br>
<br>
The other drugs you listed there Rob, you wouldn't find casual users.  You'll find people that claim to be casual users, but I assure you they all feel some sort of impact, as do their familys, from the usage.  I choose Marijuana, because the effects are less than Alchohal, a drug that is currently legal.  You will kill more brain cells, do more damage to your liver, drinking than smoking pot. <br>
<br>
The problem with legalization is the process.  What senator is going to run for office as &quot;legalize pot&quot; as their platform, when their are so many more serious issues.  It's a double standard because legalization of the substance would be a lot of work.  It was easy to criminalize it, but decriminilization would mean looking at a huge amount of people in jail today, and talking about overturning convictions.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Civil rigths and recreational drug use do not equate </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Why not?  It's my body.<br>
<br>
The government says you can put alchohal and nicotine in your body, because the effects unless abused are not life threatening or a general danger to society.<br>
<br>
Why can't I smoke pot then? Simply because the government is telling me what I can and can't injest? Even though what I want to smoke is less damaging than the other two?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  If it's a law you don't agree with.. don't break it... abolish it.. but respect it till you do. </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
- In most states it is illegal to commit adultry.  <br>
- In Arizona, Sorority houses are illegal.  You see, any house where more than 3 women are living is considered a brothel.<br>
- Oral Sex in Arizona is illegal, even between married couples.<br>
<br>
3 examples of absurd laws, that are not enforced, that you will never see abolished.  No one is going ot run on the &quot;Allow Blowjobs&quot; platform, not when Healthcare and Education are such pressing issues.<br>
<br>
So why doesn't the government want pot ot be legal?<br>
<br>
- Tobacco companies.  Tobacco can't really be home grown very well.  The concentrations of nicotine are not high enough, which is why Tobacco vats are sprayed down with Nicotine to add ot the content.  Also Tobacco tastes liek shit when smoked, so they have to add all sorts of other fillers and flavors.<br>
<br>
Pot on the otherhand can grow almost anywhere.  The cultivation portion is very simple, so simple that people could likely grow all the pot they would need in their backyards next to the rose bushes.<br>
<br>
So it's all about money.  Sure legally bought pot would bring the Government money, but lots of people would grow their own.  This doesn't help line anyone's pockets with more money, and if you can't get more money for something, why support it?<br>
<br>
Our laws, our government, it all revolves around Capitalism. If something comes up that might take away from the mighty dollar, the government is forced by the major corporations to essentially do what they say.  This is why, we still use the combustion engine.  Doesn't it seem weird to anyone else with these super-advances made in computers to make them 1000X more efficient than they were when they first came out; that we still are using the SAME combustion engines that get the worst possible fuel economy?<br>
<br>
In science class, 9th grade. we learned about a super-car that traveled from Florida-Los Angelas on one tank of gas.  Car was a Cadillac.<br>
<br>
The guy that invented this carborator; him and his family just disappeared, were never heard from again. The car and the pattons lost and tied up.<br>
<br>
It's sickening.  So many of our laws are just there for the rich to continue their strangle hold on the rest of us.<br>
